text: Rinzia polystemonea, commonly known as the desert rock myrtle, is a plant species of the family Myrtaceae endemic to Western Australia. The shrub is found in the far eastern Goldfields-Esperance region of Western Australia near the border with South Australia and the Northern Territory. ==References== polystemonea Category:Endemic flora of Western Australia Category:Myrtales of Australia Category:Rosids of Western Australia Category:Taxa named by Ferdinand von Mueller Category:Taxa named by Barbara Lynette Rye
